1.0beta2 - [RELEASEDATE]

Global changes
==============

- Refactored the whole package to fit into the unified layout.
- Switched to the use of structs where it made sense: ezcConsoleOptionRule,
  ezcConsoleOutputFormat, ezcConsoleOutputFormats, ezcConsoleOutputOptions,
  ezcConsoleProgressbarOptions, eczConsoleTableOptions.
- Migrated to use overloading property access - __get(),__set(),__isset() -
  where possible (more convenient).

Class based changes
===================

ezcConsoleOutput
----------------

- Renamed ezcConsoleOutput::styleText() to ezcConsoleOutput::formatText().
- Added convenience method outputLine() to ezcConsoleOutput. This one adds a
  line break after outputting the desired text and works even without any
  parameters.

ezcConsoleParamter
------------------

- Unified handling of parameter names, short and long parameters are now
  handled equally without their prefix everywhere.
- Enhanced eczConsoleParameter::getHelp() method by a filter parameter.
- Fix bug with argument handling and non-value parameters.
- Fixed bug with submitting multiple parameters of the same name without value.
- Added a new class ezcConsoleOption to represent an option (instead of using
  an array).
- Renamed ezcConsoleParameter to ezcConsoleInput (makes more sense, since
  Parameter sounded like an acronym for Option).
- Migrated ezcConsoleParameter class to use the new structs.
- Reworked handling of default values for ezcComponentOption.
- Added new setting "mandatory" to indicate that an option has to be submitted
  on every use of a program.
- Renamed fromString() to registerOptionString().

ezcConsoleTable
---------------

- Implemented classes ezcConsoleTableRow and ezcConsoleTableCell. These allow
  a new, innovative and very convenient way to create and customize console
  based tables: "$table[0][];" creates a new cell, "$table[2][]->format =
  'important';" creates a new cell and set's it's format to 'important',
  "$table[2]->align = ezcConsoleTable::ALIGN_CENTER;" set's the default
  alignment for row 3 to be center oriented. 
- Implemented cell, row and table based format and alignment settings.
- Implemented real inheritence of format and alignment values. The inheritence
  works like this: "Is the value not 'default' on cell level" ? true: "Use
  this value" false: "Is the value not 'default' on row level? true: "Use this
  value" false: "Use the value defined as table default".
- Added borderFormat property to rows to set a specific format for use of the
  row border.

ezcConsoleStatusbar
-------------------

- Updated to use new structs.

ezcConsoleProgressbar
---------------------

- Updated to use new structs.


1.0beta1 - [RELEASEDATE]

- Initial release of this package.
